{"type":null,"faqId":26422,"title":"Saving Your Mobile Data Traffic","answer":"<p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:center\" align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333\">Saving Your Mobile Data Traffic</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#666666;\">Why do\nsmartphones consume so much mobile data traffic? What should we do to save the\nmobile data traffic?</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Times New Roman','serif';color:red;\n\">Why do smartphones consume so much mobile data traffic?</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Smartphones\nrequire data connection for system updates and data synchronization. Some\nmalicious applications, games, or embedded advertisements also access the\nInternet in the background. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Times New Roman','serif';color:red;\n\">What should we do to prevent excessive mobile data\nconsumption in the background?</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:21.0pt;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:.25in;text-align:left;\ntext-indent:-.25in;\n\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#9966FF;\"><span>1.<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#9966FF;\">Disable\nauto-sync on your phone.</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Your phone can\nautomatically back up important data to the cloud, which incurs a lot of mobile\ndata traffic consumption, especially when auto-upload of photos is enabled. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:21.0pt;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:.25in;text-align:left;\ntext-indent:-.25in;\n\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#9966FF;\"><span>2.<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#9966FF;\">Disable mobile\ndata when you do not need it. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Drag the status\nbar downward to display the shortcut switch panel. Touch the mobile data switch\nto disable mobile data. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:21.0pt;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:.25in;text-align:left;\ntext-indent:-.25in;\n\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#9966FF;\"><span>3.<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#9966FF;\">Disable mobile\ndata when you are using Wi-Fi.</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Your phone\nautomatically switches to the mobile data connection when Wi-Fi reception is\npoor, incurring mobile data traffic without your knowledge. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:21.0pt;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:.25in;text-align:left;\ntext-indent:-.25in;\n\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#9966FF;\"><span>4.<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#9966FF;\">Enable mobile\ndata traffic monitoring and restriction.</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">The Phone Manager pre-installed in Huawei\nphones provides real-time mobile data traffic monitoring. You can view your\nmobile data usage, enable warning thresholds, and prevent some applications\nfrom accessing your mobile data. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Note: You are not advised to root your\nphone because it may void your phone's warranty, make the system operation\nunstable, and incur unknown errors.</span></p>\n<br>\n</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"821","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1433164870000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":3,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Saving Your Mobile Data Traffic","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}